00:36:14.875 --> 00:36:16.810
lets you know
when you're getting close.

00:36:16.844 --> 00:36:18.178
[chime]

00:36:18.212 --> 00:36:20.614
To make it even less likely
to lose your AirPods,

00:36:20.647 --> 00:36:22.683
you can now receive
a Separation Alert

00:36:22.716 --> 00:36:24.751
to notify you if you leave
your AirPods behind.

00:36:25.919 --> 00:36:28.422
Finally, last year,
we introduced spatial audio

00:36:28.455 --> 00:36:31.058
with dynamic head tracking
for AirPods Pro

00:36:31.425 --> 00:36:33.360
and then elevated the experience
even further

00:36:33.393 --> 00:36:35.495
with the high fidelity audio
of AirPods Max.

00:36:36.797 --> 00:36:38.732
Enabled by computational audio,

00:36:38.765 --> 00:36:40.901
the three-dimensional
theater-like sound

00:36:40.934 --> 00:36:42.703
really makes movies
come to life.

00:36:43.370 --> 00:36:47.474
This fall, we're excited
to extend spatial audio to tvOS.

00:36:47.508 --> 00:36:50.043
So now you can enjoy the full
surround experience,

00:36:50.077 --> 00:36:51.845
tuned for the big screen
in your living room,

00:36:51.879 --> 00:36:54.147
without disturbing
the rest of the house.

00:36:54.181 --> 00:36:55.649
And with dynamic head tracking,

00:36:55.682 --> 00:36:58.252
it properly responds
as you move about the room.

00:36:58.285 --> 00:37:01.121
We're also bringing spatial
audio with dynamic head tracking

00:37:01.154 --> 00:37:03.891
to macOS on our new
M1 powered Macs

00:37:03.924 --> 00:37:08.095
so you can enjoy spatial
on all of your devices.

00:37:08.128 --> 00:37:10.764
In addition, we recently
announced spatial audio

00:37:10.797 --> 00:37:12.299
for Apple Music
with the incredible

00:37:12.332 --> 00:37:15.502
multi-dimensional sound
experience of Dolby Atmos.

00:37:15.536 --> 00:37:18.305
And we're excited that
it's available starting today

00:37:18.338 --> 00:37:20.307
with albums from some
of your favorite artists,

00:37:20.340 --> 00:37:25.312
like Ariana Grande, The Weeknd,
J Balvin, and Kacey Musgraves.

00:37:26.580 --> 00:37:28.782
With the benefits
of Conversation Boost,

00:37:28.815 --> 00:37:30.484
the convenience of Find My,

00:37:30.517 --> 00:37:32.886
and the enhanced experience
with spatial audio,

00:37:32.920 --> 00:37:34.488
there are some great
new features

00:37:34.521 --> 00:37:35.989
coming to the AirPods family.

00:37:36.557 --> 00:37:38.458
Now back to you, Craig.

00:37:39.660 --> 00:37:44.097
[singer] ♪ Just like magic,
oh, yeah ♪

00:37:44.131 --> 00:37:47.634
[Craig] It's time to talk about
iPadOS.

00:37:47.668 --> 00:37:50.070
iPad is an incredibly
versatile device,

00:37:50.103 --> 00:37:52.105
with its unique blend
of mobility,

00:37:52.139 --> 00:37:56.143
innovative technologies,
and touch-first user experience,

00:37:56.176 --> 00:37:59.880
and this experience
is powered by iPadOS.

00:37:59.913 --> 00:38:03.083
With iPadOS,
we build distinct capabilities

00:38:03.116 --> 00:38:04.685
that make it possible for iPad

00:38:04.718 --> 00:38:06.920
to become whatever
you need it to be,

00:38:06.954 --> 00:38:08.789
like when you're browsing
your photos

00:38:08.822 --> 00:38:11.892
and iPad becomes an album
of your most precious memories,

00:38:11.925 --> 00:38:13.527
held right in your hands;

00:38:13.560 --> 00:38:15.062
or when you pick up
Apple Pencil

00:38:15.095 --> 00:38:17.898
and it becomes your notepad,
a markup tool,

00:38:17.931 --> 00:38:19.800
or a canvas for new artwork;

00:38:19.833 --> 00:38:22.135
or when you attach
a keyboard and trackpad,

00:38:22.169 --> 00:38:24.104
and it becomes
a powerful new way

00:38:24.137 --> 00:38:26.306
to work on your most important
documents.

00:38:26.340 --> 00:38:28.208
This unique set of capabilities

00:38:28.242 --> 00:38:30.811
mean you get things done
right in the moment

00:38:30.844 --> 00:38:32.045
and can seamlessly move

00:38:32.079 --> 00:38:34.481
from capturing
and working on your ideas

00:38:34.515 --> 00:38:35.516
to sharing them.

00:38:35.883 --> 00:38:37.584
With iPadOS 15,

00:38:37.618 --> 00:38:40.220
we're taking
this versatility further,

00:38:40.254 --> 00:38:44.057
making iPad even more capable
and more intuitive,

00:38:44.091 --> 00:38:47.794
and we started right
on the home screen with widgets.

00:38:47.828 --> 00:38:50.464
They offer beautiful,
glance-able information

00:38:50.497 --> 00:38:51.865
at just the right moments,

00:38:51.899 --> 00:38:54.968
and this year,
we have a big update.

00:38:55.002 --> 00:38:56.403
Now you can freely place widgets

00:38:56.436 --> 00:38:58.338
among the apps
on your home screen.

00:38:58.372 --> 00:38:59.973
This is a huge deal!

00:39:00.007 --> 00:39:02.142
Let me show you how it works.

00:39:02.176 --> 00:39:03.510
Okay.

00:39:03.544 --> 00:39:05.879
Here I am on the home screen.

00:39:05.913 --> 00:39:07.848
You can see that I already have
a few widgets

00:39:07.881 --> 00:39:09.216
placed along the top.

00:39:09.249 --> 00:39:11.752
Let's start by adding a widget.

00:39:11.785 --> 00:39:14.555
I'll bring up
the widget gallery.

00:39:14.588 --> 00:39:16.356
Here you'll notice
some new widgets

00:39:16.390 --> 00:39:18.325
like the beautiful new
Find My widget

00:39:18.358 --> 00:39:19.526
and the Contacts widget

00:39:19.560 --> 00:39:21.295
which helps you reach family
and friends

00:39:21.328 --> 00:39:22.863
with just a tap.

00:39:22.896 --> 00:39:26.433
Let's find a good spot for this,
towards the top here.

00:39:26.466 --> 00:39:30.037
Now, I'll go back to the gallery
and grab the Parcel widget

00:39:30.070 --> 00:39:32.005
for tracking
my incoming packages

00:39:32.039 --> 00:39:33.373
right on the home screen.

00:39:33.407 --> 00:39:35.409
Perfect.

00:39:35.442 --> 00:39:39.246
Now, of course a bigger canvas
means more room for widgets,

00:39:39.279 --> 00:39:42.182
so we're adding a new,
larger format for widgets

00:39:42.216 --> 00:39:44.751
designed just for iPad's
larger display.

00:39:44.785 --> 00:39:46.720
Here's the new
Apple TV widget.

00:39:46.753 --> 00:39:49.389
I can easily dive into
my favorite shows with a tap,

00:39:49.423 --> 00:39:52.025
and here's my gaming page.

00:39:52.059 --> 00:39:53.460
The new Game Center widget

00:39:53.493 --> 00:39:55.295
lets me jump
into my games faster

00:39:55.329 --> 00:39:57.631
and discover what to play
with friends.

00:39:57.664 --> 00:40:00.133
And check out the new
large-size Photos widget.

00:39:57.664 --> 00:40:00.133
And check out the new
large-size Photos widget.

00:40:00.167 --> 00:40:04.304
It really puts my favorite
photos front and center,

00:40:04.338 --> 00:40:06.306
and with this larger
Files widget,

00:40:06.340 --> 00:40:08.976
I can keep tabs
on all of my work projects.

00:40:09.009 --> 00:40:11.512
Now, with pages full of
these great widgets,

00:40:11.545 --> 00:40:13.547
some of my less frequently used
apps

00:40:13.580 --> 00:40:15.849
have gotten pushed
to later pages.

00:40:15.883 --> 00:40:19.486
We wanted to make it easier
to get to all of your apps,

00:40:19.520 --> 00:40:23.056
so we brought App Library
to iPad.

00:40:23.090 --> 00:40:24.992
You can see all my apps
are here,

00:40:25.025 --> 00:40:26.727
automatically categorized
for me.

00:40:26.760 --> 00:40:30.464
And what's really cool is we
built access to App Library

00:40:30.497 --> 00:40:31.832
right into the Dock,

00:40:31.865 --> 00:40:33.667
no matter where you are,

00:40:33.700 --> 00:40:36.603
you can always get to your apps.

00:40:36.637 --> 00:40:38.539
And now that you have
App Library,

00:40:38.572 --> 00:40:42.543
you can hide pages
that you no longer need...

00:40:42.576 --> 00:40:45.412
just like this.

00:40:45.445 --> 00:40:49.383
And even reorder them
right from here.

00:40:49.416 --> 00:40:52.085
That's widgets and App Library.

00:40:52.119 --> 00:40:54.121
We think this is going to change
how you get information

00:40:54.154 --> 00:40:57.291
and access all your apps
on iPad.

00:40:57.324 --> 00:40:59.226
We also have a major update

00:40:59.259 --> 00:41:02.129
for another key part
of the iPadOS experience:

00:41:02.162 --> 00:41:03.931
multitasking.

00:41:03.964 --> 00:41:06.433
This year, we've made it
easier to discover,

00:41:06.466 --> 00:41:09.603
easier to use,
and even more powerful.

00:41:09.636 --> 00:41:12.439
To give you a closer look,
here's Shubham.

00:41:12.472 --> 00:41:13.574
[Shubham] Thanks, Craig.

00:41:13.607 --> 00:41:16.543
In iPadOS 15,
there's a new control

00:41:16.577 --> 00:41:18.345
that appears
at the top of your apps.

00:41:19.246 --> 00:41:22.082
Tapping on it reveals
the multitasking menu.

00:41:22.115 --> 00:41:24.618
From here, I can take an app,
full-screen,

00:41:24.651 --> 00:41:27.020
or work with two apps
at the same time

00:41:27.054 --> 00:41:28.856
by creating a Split View
or Slide Over.

00:41:28.889 --> 00:41:31.425
I'll tap on the Split View icon,

00:41:31.458 --> 00:41:33.293
and the app slides
to the edge of the screen,

00:41:33.327 --> 00:41:35.696
giving me quick access
to my home screen,

00:41:35.729 --> 00:41:37.564
where I can easily select
from any of my apps.

00:41:37.598 --> 00:41:41.134
I've been working on a podcast,
so I'll choose Ferrite.

00:41:41.168 --> 00:41:43.604
And now I can work
with Ferrite and Notes

00:41:43.637 --> 00:41:45.072
at the same time in Split View.

00:41:45.105 --> 00:41:48.375
It's also really easy
to switch apps in Split View.

00:41:48.408 --> 00:41:51.445
If I want to replace Ferrite,
I just swipe down,

00:41:51.478 --> 00:41:52.946
and Notes moves aside,

00:41:52.980 --> 00:41:55.215
letting me pick another app
from the home screen.

00:41:55.249 --> 00:41:57.050
Let's select Mail.

00:41:58.318 --> 00:41:59.953
This works exactly the same way

00:41:59.987 --> 00:42:02.155
to choose a new app
from either side of the screen.

00:42:02.189 --> 00:42:04.625
And we brought the same
ease of multitasking

00:42:04.658 --> 00:42:06.693
to apps with multiple windows.

00:42:06.727 --> 00:42:09.930
In Mail, I can touch and hold
on this message

00:42:09.963 --> 00:42:12.599
to open it
centered on my screen.

00:42:12.633 --> 00:42:14.968
This allows me to read
the entire email

00:42:15.002 --> 00:42:17.371
without leaving my current view.

00:42:17.404 --> 00:42:20.374
And I have the same
multitasking controls here, too,

00:42:20.407 --> 00:42:23.510
so I can easily move this
into Split View or Slide Over.

00:42:23.544 --> 00:42:26.713
But I want to save this email
and come back to it later.

00:42:26.747 --> 00:42:29.850
So I can just swipe down
to minimize it

00:42:29.883 --> 00:42:32.019
into a new area
we're calling the Shelf.

00:42:32.052 --> 00:42:35.756
The Shelf gives me easy access
to all open windows of an app.

00:42:35.789 --> 00:42:38.158
Let's go to Safari,
and you'll see that

00:42:38.192 --> 00:42:41.028
the Shelf appears automatically
when I switch apps.

00:42:41.061 --> 00:42:43.730
I often have a lot
of Safari windows open,

00:42:43.764 --> 00:42:46.033
many in Split View
paired with other apps,

00:42:46.066 --> 00:42:49.536
and now I can just tap
to quickly switch between them.

00:42:49.570 --> 00:42:53.774
I can also add or remove windows
right here from the Shelf.

00:42:53.807 --> 00:42:56.610
We've also made the App Switcher
even more powerful.

00:42:56.643 --> 00:42:58.412
I can now create a Split view

00:42:58.445 --> 00:43:01.682
just by dragging one app
over another.

00:43:01.715 --> 00:43:04.585
So that's multitasking
in iPadOS 15.

00:43:04.618 --> 00:43:06.553
Now back to you, Craig.

00:43:06.587 --> 00:43:08.555
[Craig] Thanks, Shubham.

00:43:08.589 --> 00:43:10.190
These new multitasking features

00:43:10.224 --> 00:43:12.059
will help our users
be more productive

00:43:12.092 --> 00:43:14.728
and do even more on their iPad,

00:43:14.761 --> 00:43:16.063
and what's really cool

00:43:16.096 --> 00:43:18.999
is we now have a new set
of keyboard shortcuts

00:43:19.032 --> 00:43:22.703
that let you do all of this
without lifting a finger.

00:43:22.736 --> 00:43:26.106
iPadOS 15 also gives you
more powerful ways

00:43:26.139 --> 00:43:29.843
to capture and organize
your information with Notes.

00:43:29.877 --> 00:43:32.246
This year we're adding
powerful new features

00:43:32.279 --> 00:43:34.815
for collaboration
and organization.

00:43:34.848 --> 00:43:37.518
First, we're adding mentions.

00:43:37.551 --> 00:43:39.353
Just mention someone
in a shared note

00:43:39.386 --> 00:43:42.189
and they'll get a notification
linking them back.

00:43:42.222 --> 00:43:44.691
There's also an all-new
Activity View

00:43:44.725 --> 00:43:46.226
that quickly shows you
what's changed

00:43:46.260 --> 00:43:48.128
in a shared note
while you were away.

00:43:48.161 --> 00:43:51.198
And to give users new ways
to organize their notes,

00:43:51.231 --> 00:43:53.066
we're adding tags.

00:43:53.100 --> 00:43:55.235
You can add a tag
anywhere in your note

00:43:55.269 --> 00:43:58.539
then use the new Tag Browser
to quickly find your notes.

00:43:58.572 --> 00:44:01.909
But sometimes you just want
to quickly jot down a note

00:44:01.942 --> 00:44:04.077
to remember
something important for later,

00:44:04.111 --> 00:44:06.847
and that's why
we're taking Notes system-wide

00:44:06.880 --> 00:44:09.716
with a feature
we call Quick Note.

00:44:09.750 --> 00:44:12.319
Quick Note is a fast and easy
way to get to a note,

00:44:12.352 --> 00:44:13.887
no matter what you're doing.

00:44:13.921 --> 00:44:15.889
Here's Will to show you
how it works.

00:44:16.423 --> 00:44:17.524
[Will] Thanks, Craig.

00:44:17.558 --> 00:44:19.693
Starting a Quick Note is easy.

00:44:19.726 --> 00:44:21.895
When I swipe,
the note appears

00:44:21.929 --> 00:44:23.497
out of the corner of the screen.

00:44:23.530 --> 00:44:25.232
Now that I've started a note,

00:44:25.265 --> 00:44:28.135
I can type or write
with Apple Pencil.

00:44:28.168 --> 00:44:31.772
It's perfect for jotting down
something like a phone number.

00:44:31.805 --> 00:44:35.909
And when I'm done,
I just swipe it away.

00:44:35.943 --> 00:44:38.212
Let's open Safari.

00:44:38.245 --> 00:44:40.314
What's super cool
about Quick Note

00:44:40.347 --> 00:44:42.850
is that it's aware
of the app I'm using.

00:44:42.883 --> 00:44:46.053
I'll start a new Quick Note
on top of Safari...

00:44:49.356 --> 00:44:52.526
...and now I can easily add
a link from the website

00:44:52.559 --> 00:44:54.361
into my Quick Note.

00:44:54.394 --> 00:44:57.831
I can tap this link anytime
to return to this exact site.

00:44:57.865 --> 00:45:00.968
Let's go to a website
I added a link to earlier.

00:45:01.001 --> 00:45:03.470
A small thumbnail
pops up in the corner

00:45:03.504 --> 00:45:06.640
that allows me to quickly
get back to my Quick Note

00:45:06.673 --> 00:45:09.009
containing any useful
information I found.

00:45:10.277 --> 00:45:13.080
You'll notice there's text
highlighted on the page.

00:45:13.113 --> 00:45:15.616
And I added this text
to my Quick Note.

00:45:15.649 --> 00:45:17.751
And tapping on a link
from a highlight

00:45:17.784 --> 00:45:20.420
takes me right to
the content on the page.

00:45:20.454 --> 00:45:23.690
I can add a link
from almost any app I'm using,

00:45:23.724 --> 00:45:25.792
including third-party apps.

00:45:25.826 --> 00:45:28.428
Here's a link from Yelp,
and if I tap,

00:45:28.462 --> 00:45:31.064
it takes me right
to the restaurant listing.

00:45:31.098 --> 00:45:33.300
I can swipe
across my Quick Note

00:45:33.333 --> 00:45:35.135
to see my most recent ones.

00:45:35.169 --> 00:45:37.905
And anytime I want to see
all my Quick Notes,

00:45:37.938 --> 00:45:42.176
I can find them right
where you'd expect, in Notes.

00:45:42.209 --> 00:45:43.744
Now back to Craig.

00:45:43.777 --> 00:45:45.445
[Craig] Thanks, Will.

00:45:45.479 --> 00:45:47.080
So that's Quick Note,

00:45:47.114 --> 00:45:49.816
a new way to capture
information anywhere.

00:45:49.850 --> 00:45:53.053
Quick Notes can be created
on iPadOS and macOS,

00:45:53.086 --> 00:45:56.323
and you can access
and edit them later on iOS.

00:45:56.356 --> 00:45:59.193
Now let's talk about Translate.

00:45:59.760 --> 00:46:02.629
In just one year, Translate
has already helped users

00:46:02.663 --> 00:46:05.098
make billions of translations
on iOS.

00:46:05.132 --> 00:46:08.569
So we're excited to bring
Translate to iPad,

00:46:08.602 --> 00:46:12.172
with experiences that leverage
iPad's unique capabilities,

00:46:12.206 --> 00:46:14.441
like practicing handwriting
in another language

00:46:14.474 --> 00:46:16.276
with Apple Pencil

00:46:16.310 --> 00:46:18.178
or translating
right next to your document

00:46:18.212 --> 00:46:19.513
with Split View.

00:46:19.546 --> 00:46:22.249
And Translate was designed
for conversations.

00:46:22.282 --> 00:46:24.618
So we're making conversations
feel easier

00:46:24.651 --> 00:46:27.855
and even more natural
with Auto Translate.

00:46:28.388 --> 00:46:30.657
Auto Translate detects
when you're speaking,

00:46:30.691 --> 00:46:32.226
and in which language,

00:46:32.259 --> 00:46:34.962
so no one needs to tap a button
to respond.

00:46:34.995 --> 00:46:36.997
Just speak
and let Translate do the rest.

00:46:37.030 --> 00:46:40.868
We're also excited to announce
system-wide translation.

00:46:40.901 --> 00:46:42.836
So you can translate
text anywhere.

00:46:42.870 --> 00:46:45.839
Just select the text
and tap Translate.

00:46:45.873 --> 00:46:49.776
With Live Text, you can even
translate text in a photo.

00:46:49.810 --> 00:46:51.745
System-wide translation
is available

00:46:51.778 --> 00:46:54.481
on iPadOS, iOS, and macOS,

00:46:54.515 --> 00:46:56.984
and of course,
you can download languages

00:46:57.017 --> 00:46:59.553
to use all of these features
on-device.

00:46:59.586 --> 00:47:01.522
Whether you're working
on a document

00:47:01.555 --> 00:47:03.123
or meeting with someone,

00:47:03.156 --> 00:47:06.293
Translate makes iPad
even more powerful.

00:47:06.326 --> 00:47:10.030
Now let's talk
about Swift Playgrounds

00:47:10.063 --> 00:47:13.300
and how it's bringing a whole
new dimension of productivity

00:47:13.333 --> 00:47:14.535
to iPad.

00:47:14.568 --> 00:47:17.771
Swift Playgrounds is a great way
to learn to code

00:47:17.804 --> 00:47:20.140
through a series
of Apple-designed lesson plans

00:47:20.174 --> 00:47:22.442
that are interactive and fun.

00:47:22.476 --> 00:47:25.012
This year we're taking it
even further

00:47:25.045 --> 00:47:28.315
by adding the ability
to build apps on iPad.

00:47:28.348 --> 00:47:30.751
You build these apps
with Swift UI,

00:47:30.784 --> 00:47:32.386
which makes development easy.

00:47:32.419 --> 00:47:34.421
The code you write
is immediately reflected

00:47:34.454 --> 00:47:35.989
in a live preview of your app.

00:47:36.023 --> 00:47:39.092
This new project type
even works with Xcode on Mac.

00:47:39.126 --> 00:47:42.462
Swift Playgrounds now supports
improved code completion,

00:47:42.496 --> 00:47:43.764
so you can just start typing

00:47:43.797 --> 00:47:46.633
and quickly add the suggestion
to your code.

00:47:46.667 --> 00:47:48.569
You also have access
to the whole library

00:47:48.602 --> 00:47:50.170
of UI components

00:47:50.204 --> 00:47:52.372
