01:00:06.006 --> 01:00:08.709
[Francoise] This is the start
of something incredible.

01:00:08.742 --> 01:00:11.478
It’s the spark,
and now it’s like fire

01:00:15.148 --> 01:00:17.985
[Sumbul] This is just one of the
many inspiring stories out there

01:00:18.018 --> 01:00:20.621
and is a testament
to the innovative work happening

01:00:20.654 --> 01:00:22.422
in the medical community.

01:00:22.456 --> 01:00:24.658
A critical part
of taking care of yourself

01:00:24.691 --> 01:00:26.793
is monitoring changes
in your health,

01:00:26.827 --> 01:00:29.429
which can be subtle
and easy to miss over time.

01:00:29.463 --> 01:00:32.199
So this year, we're offering
three new features

01:00:32.232 --> 01:00:34.868
to help you to identify,
measure,

01:00:34.902 --> 01:00:37.704
and understand those changes,
and here's Adeeti

01:00:37.738 --> 01:00:39.840
to tell you about the first
of these features.

01:00:41.275 --> 01:00:43.710
[Adeeti] Let's start
with mobility.

01:00:43.744 --> 01:00:45.045
The way that you move and walk

01:00:45.078 --> 01:00:48.048
can indicate balance issues
and gait impairment.

01:00:48.081 --> 01:00:51.151
This is the leading cause
of falls in adults.

01:00:51.185 --> 01:00:54.421
Currently, fall risk
is assessed by a care provider

01:00:54.454 --> 01:00:57.624
through a questionnaire
and an in-person evaluation.

01:00:57.658 --> 01:00:59.960
But this can miss out
on your everyday movement,

01:00:59.993 --> 01:01:02.663
so important changes
can go unnoticed.

01:01:02.696 --> 01:01:05.866
Your iPhone already captures
mobility data as you walk

01:01:05.899 --> 01:01:08.302
with scientifically validated
metrics.

01:01:08.335 --> 01:01:09.970
We're building on this
to introduce

01:01:10.003 --> 01:01:13.774
a completely new way
to assess your risk of falling

01:01:13.807 --> 01:01:16.844
called Walking Steadiness.

01:01:16.877 --> 01:01:18.278
For the first time ever,

01:01:18.312 --> 01:01:21.515
you can get insight
if your fall risk increases

01:01:21.548 --> 01:01:24.351
and take action early
to improve your steadiness.

01:01:24.384 --> 01:01:27.554
Let's take a quick look at some
of the science behind this.

01:01:27.588 --> 01:01:31.191
As you walk with your iPhone,
the built-in motion sensors

01:01:31.225 --> 01:01:35.996
automatically measure how fast
and how evenly you walk,

01:01:36.029 --> 01:01:39.766
the length of your steps,
and the timing of each step,

01:01:39.800 --> 01:01:43.437
right down to how often you have
both feet on the ground.

01:01:43.470 --> 01:01:46.206
Combined, these metrics
provide powerful insight

01:01:46.240 --> 01:01:49.810
on changes in your balance,
stability, and coordination.

01:01:50.577 --> 01:01:51.979
We used real-world data

01:01:52.012 --> 01:01:53.580
from the Apple
Heart & Movement Study,

01:01:53.614 --> 01:01:56.817
with over 100,000 participants
across all ages.

01:01:56.850 --> 01:02:00.287
This is the largest data set
ever used to study fall risk,

01:02:00.320 --> 01:02:03.824
and it's helped create this
first of its kind health metric.

01:02:03.857 --> 01:02:06.827
You can view your Walking
Steadiness in the Health app.

01:02:06.860 --> 01:02:08.996
You'll see a classification
of "OK"

01:02:09.029 --> 01:02:11.732
if the metrics show that
you're stable while walking.

01:02:11.765 --> 01:02:14.034
You can see how
your Walking Steadiness

01:02:14.067 --> 01:02:16.036
may change as the months go by

01:02:16.069 --> 01:02:18.505
and receive a notification
if your steadiness is low

01:02:18.539 --> 01:02:21.675
or very low and you're
at increased risk of falling.

01:02:21.708 --> 01:02:24.244
You can also learn how
to improve your steadiness.

01:02:24.278 --> 01:02:27.414
There are movement exercises
right in the Health app,

01:02:27.447 --> 01:02:30.317
and these can help you increase
your strength and balance

01:02:30.350 --> 01:02:32.853
and reduce your risk of falling.

01:02:32.886 --> 01:02:34.388
Now back to Sumbul

01:02:34.421 --> 01:02:37.591
to tell you about another way
to monitor health changes.

01:02:38.492 --> 01:02:40.727
[Sumbul] You can already
review lab results

01:02:40.761 --> 01:02:42.763
like your cholesterol
right in the Health app.

01:02:42.796 --> 01:02:46.800
In the U.S. alone, 14 billion
clinical laboratory tests

01:02:46.834 --> 01:02:48.101
are performed each year.

01:02:48.135 --> 01:02:51.071
That is a lot of information
to keep track of.

01:02:51.104 --> 01:02:53.006
When you see your own results
come in,

01:02:53.040 --> 01:02:55.342
it can be hard to understand
what these tests mean

01:02:55.375 --> 01:02:56.510
or what has changed.

01:02:57.177 --> 01:03:00.347
The Health app will now include
detailed descriptions

01:03:00.380 --> 01:03:03.183
to help you better understand
your lab data.

01:03:03.217 --> 01:03:06.119
For example, when you
receive a cholesterol result,

01:03:06.153 --> 01:03:09.256
you can now see that the LDL
is a bad cholesterol

01:03:09.289 --> 01:03:12.226
and having too much may put you
at risk for heart disease.

01:03:12.259 --> 01:03:14.161
You can also now see
whether your labs

01:03:14.194 --> 01:03:15.829
are within expected ranges.

01:03:15.863 --> 01:03:17.631
Together, these views
will help you

01:03:17.664 --> 01:03:20.534
get even more meaning
from your lab results.

01:03:20.567 --> 01:03:22.736
Many health changes
happen over time,

01:03:22.769 --> 01:03:24.171
so to better understand
your health

01:03:24.204 --> 01:03:28.408
even more holistically,
we're introducing Trends.

01:03:28.442 --> 01:03:30.811
You'll get insight
on long-term changes

01:03:30.844 --> 01:03:33.614
across areas such as steps,
resting heart rate,

01:03:33.647 --> 01:03:36.216
blood glucose, sleep,
and much more.

01:03:36.250 --> 01:03:38.018
You'll also be alerted
when there's a new trend

01:03:38.051 --> 01:03:39.720
in your data,
which may be something

01:03:39.753 --> 01:03:41.255
you want to monitor more closely

01:03:41.288 --> 01:03:42.856
or even discuss
with your physician.

01:03:42.890 --> 01:03:44.625
So if you're getting
more daily walks in,

01:03:44.658 --> 01:03:46.260
your health summary will show

01:03:46.293 --> 01:03:47.794
that your steps taken
have increased

01:03:47.828 --> 01:03:49.096
over the last few months.

01:03:49.129 --> 01:03:51.265
This is a great way
to celebrate progress

01:03:51.298 --> 01:03:52.900
towards meeting
your health goals

01:03:52.933 --> 01:03:55.402
and a powerful new way
to get early insight

01:03:55.435 --> 01:03:56.937
into potential health issues.

01:03:56.970 --> 01:03:59.139
With Trends,
Walking Steadiness,

01:03:59.173 --> 01:04:00.908
and a better Labs experience,

01:04:00.941 --> 01:04:03.243
you have three new ways
to see changes

01:04:03.277 --> 01:04:04.978
in your overall health.

01:04:05.012 --> 01:04:07.915
Another really important
part of managing your health

01:04:07.948 --> 01:04:10.150
is having meaningful
conversations with your doctor.

01:04:10.184 --> 01:04:13.420
During your visit, physicians
look at your vitals and labs

01:04:13.453 --> 01:04:15.756
but will also ask you about
everyday health activities

01:04:15.789 --> 01:04:17.925
like exercise and sleep.

01:04:17.958 --> 01:04:19.726
And patients can often
have difficulty

01:04:19.760 --> 01:04:21.562
remembering all these details.

01:04:21.595 --> 01:04:24.798
But the Health app has all of
this valuable information,

01:04:24.831 --> 01:04:27.034
so, to support this
conversation,

01:04:27.067 --> 01:04:29.937
you can now share
health data that you choose

01:04:29.970 --> 01:04:33.106
with your healthcare provider
in a private way.

01:04:33.140 --> 01:04:35.776
For example, if you have a
concern about your heart health,

01:04:35.809 --> 01:04:37.778
you can now share
your heart data.

01:04:37.811 --> 01:04:39.446
This is shared securely.

01:04:39.479 --> 01:04:43.083
No one else, including Apple,
will see this information.

01:04:43.116 --> 01:04:45.352
Your doctor can then view
this data directly

01:04:45.385 --> 01:04:47.387
from their electronic
health record system

01:04:47.421 --> 01:04:50.791
and look for important trends
such as changes in activity

01:04:50.824 --> 01:04:53.460
and a history of alerts
like high heart rate.

01:04:53.493 --> 01:04:55.696
Access to this information
helps give your doctor

01:04:55.729 --> 01:04:57.831
a more complete view
of your everyday health

01:04:57.865 --> 01:04:59.433
outside of the clinic.

01:04:59.466 --> 01:05:01.768
We're so excited about
this new capability

01:05:01.802 --> 01:05:03.770
to share your data
from the Health app

01:05:03.804 --> 01:05:04.972
directly with your doctor.

01:05:05.005 --> 01:05:07.441
These electronic health
record companies in the U.S.

01:05:07.474 --> 01:05:09.309
will be the first
to support this feature,

01:05:09.343 --> 01:05:11.778
and we look forward
to expanding availability

01:05:11.812 --> 01:05:14.548
even more in the coming months.

01:05:14.581 --> 01:05:16.850
Now, for many of us,
it's not just the changes

01:05:16.884 --> 01:05:18.819
in our own health we care about.

01:05:18.852 --> 01:05:21.088
It's the health of our family
and loved ones too,

01:05:21.121 --> 01:05:23.657
whether they live with us
or far away.

01:05:23.690 --> 01:05:26.193
For some of us, that means
taking care of our kids

01:05:26.226 --> 01:05:28.428
and for others,
it's our aging parents.

01:05:28.462 --> 01:05:29.630
And for many of us,

01:05:29.663 --> 01:05:31.298
it's actually taking care of
both--

01:05:31.331 --> 01:05:33.433
generations above and below.

01:05:33.467 --> 01:05:35.636
To empower you
to care for others,

01:05:35.669 --> 01:05:37.971
we're introducing
Health Sharing,

01:05:38.005 --> 01:05:40.941
a private and secure way
to view health data,

01:05:40.974 --> 01:05:44.978
trends, and alerts for the
people most important to you.

01:05:45.012 --> 01:05:47.481
For example, I could set up
a sharing relationship

01:05:47.514 --> 01:05:49.183
with my mom,
and with her permission,

01:05:49.216 --> 01:05:51.151
I could view data
like her heart rate,

01:05:51.185 --> 01:05:52.753
activity, and labs.

01:05:52.786 --> 01:05:54.755
And just like with my own
health data,

01:05:54.788 --> 01:05:57.591
Trends proactively highlights
changes in my Mom's health data

01:05:57.624 --> 01:05:58.692
for me.

01:05:58.725 --> 01:06:00.994
I can also receive
notifications,

01:06:01.028 --> 01:06:02.863
including
high heart rate alerts,

01:06:02.896 --> 01:06:05.199
changes in mobility,
and more.

01:06:05.232 --> 01:06:08.168
And it's easy for me to connect
with her about her health.

01:06:08.202 --> 01:06:09.937
So if I see a noteworthy change

01:06:09.970 --> 01:06:11.905
like her resting heart rate
increasing,

01:06:11.939 --> 01:06:13.307
I can simply tap Messages

01:06:13.340 --> 01:06:15.776
and start a conversation
with my mom.

01:06:15.809 --> 01:06:18.412
This is a powerful new way
to stay connected

01:06:18.445 --> 01:06:20.614
to the wellbeing
of those you love.

01:06:20.647 --> 01:06:22.149
You'll have peace of mind,

01:06:22.182 --> 01:06:24.084
and they'll know they have
a trusted partner

01:06:24.117 --> 01:06:25.619
on their health journey.

01:06:25.652 --> 01:06:27.855
Since the beginning
of our work in Health,

01:06:27.888 --> 01:06:30.023
all of our health features
have been architected

01:06:30.057 --> 01:06:32.492
to keep your data secure
and protect your privacy.

01:06:32.526 --> 01:06:35.062
Your health data
is under your control

01:06:35.095 --> 01:06:37.397
and is encrypted in transit
and at rest.

01:06:37.431 --> 01:06:39.900
The permissions built into
the sharing experience

01:06:39.933 --> 01:06:41.902
give you granular control

01:06:41.935 --> 01:06:44.571
over which types of data
you share and with whom.

01:06:44.605 --> 01:06:46.607
And you can make changes
at any time

01:06:46.640 --> 01:06:48.675
right from the Sharing tab.

01:06:48.709 --> 01:06:51.512
Data you share is sent
in an encrypted form,

01:06:51.545 --> 01:06:55.616
and Apple does not have access
to any of this information.

01:06:55.649 --> 01:06:58.452
Privacy is fundamental in
the design and development

01:06:58.485 --> 01:07:00.020
across all of our
Health features.

01:07:00.053 --> 01:07:03.023
We're so excited
for what's coming in Health--

01:07:03.056 --> 01:07:05.959
a first-of-its-kind metric
to access fall risk,

01:07:05.993 --> 01:07:08.962
richer insights to understand
changes in your health,

01:07:08.996 --> 01:07:12.666
and completely new abilities
for you to privately share

01:07:12.699 --> 01:07:15.836
selected data with your doctors
and loved ones.

