With Universal Control,

01:22:34.821 --> 01:22:37.424
you can now use a single mouse
and keyboard

01:22:37.457 --> 01:22:39.459
to move between your Mac
and iPad

01:22:39.493 --> 01:22:41.461
for a seamless experience.

01:22:41.495 --> 01:22:43.864
Universal Control
is so incredible,

01:22:43.897 --> 01:22:46.099
you just have to see it
in action.

01:22:46.133 --> 01:22:48.001
Let me show it to you now.

01:22:48.669 --> 01:22:50.838
I'm putting the final touches
on an illustration

01:22:50.871 --> 01:22:52.606
here on my iPad.

01:22:52.639 --> 01:22:54.575
It's the last piece I need
to finish a presentation

01:22:54.608 --> 01:22:57.110
that I have open
on my MacBook.

01:22:57.144 --> 01:23:01.114
Now, I'll just set my iPad
down next to my Mac,

01:23:01.148 --> 01:23:02.549
and check this out.

01:23:02.583 --> 01:23:04.218
Without any other setup,

01:23:04.251 --> 01:23:06.720
I'm gonna simply move
my Mac cursor

01:23:06.753 --> 01:23:08.121
towards my iPad,

01:23:08.155 --> 01:23:10.724
and the iPad automatically
recognizes it.

01:23:10.757 --> 01:23:12.626
And if I move a bit further,

01:23:12.659 --> 01:23:15.963
boom--my cursor is now
on the iPad.

01:23:15.996 --> 01:23:17.698
How cool is that?

01:23:17.731 --> 01:23:21.435
And now I can move my cursor
back and forth effortlessly

01:23:21.468 --> 01:23:23.337
between the two.

01:23:23.370 --> 01:23:25.472
Now, it's easy to control
my iPad

01:23:25.506 --> 01:23:28.342
with just the keyboard
and trackpad on my Mac.

01:23:28.375 --> 01:23:31.278
For instance, I can click
and close this document,

01:23:31.311 --> 01:23:33.580
and flick on my trackpad

01:23:33.614 --> 01:23:35.949
to return to my iPad
home screen.

01:23:35.983 --> 01:23:39.219
And of course, I can swipe
between my pages of apps,

01:23:39.253 --> 01:23:41.388
And I can use
my MacBook's keyboard

01:23:41.421 --> 01:23:44.925
to open Spotlight
and, say, launch Notes.

01:23:44.958 --> 01:23:47.027
And I can even use command-tab

01:23:47.060 --> 01:23:49.096
to switch right back
to Procreate.

01:23:49.129 --> 01:23:50.931
This is really powerful.

01:23:50.964 --> 01:23:52.266
With Universal Control,

01:23:52.299 --> 01:23:55.869
I can even drag and drop files
between my devices.

01:23:55.903 --> 01:23:59.206
I'm just gonna take this drawing
I finished on my iPad

01:23:59.239 --> 01:24:02.943
and drop it into my Keynote
on my Mac.

01:24:03.443 --> 01:24:04.711
Awesome.

01:24:04.745 --> 01:24:06.146
For our pros out there,

01:24:06.180 --> 01:24:09.750
Universal Control works
with more than two devices.

01:24:09.783 --> 01:24:13.153
So let's add this iMac
to the mix.

01:24:13.187 --> 01:24:16.089
Now I can use the trackpad
on my MacBook

01:24:16.123 --> 01:24:19.626
to control my iMac as well.

01:24:19.660 --> 01:24:22.896
I can also switch
to my iMac's keyboard and mouse.

01:24:22.930 --> 01:24:24.965
This is so cool.
Watch this.

01:24:24.998 --> 01:24:27.868
Now, I have a title text image
I've been working on here

01:24:27.901 --> 01:24:30.337
in Procreate on my iPad.

01:24:30.370 --> 01:24:31.672
Now I'm gonna take this image

01:24:31.705 --> 01:24:35.576
and drag it across
all three devices

01:24:35.609 --> 01:24:39.980
and drop it into FinalCut.

01:24:40.013 --> 01:24:42.416
Just like that.

01:24:42.449 --> 01:24:44.685
Let's see the final product.

01:24:44.718 --> 01:24:46.119
Nice.

01:24:46.153 --> 01:24:49.156
That's a quick look
at Universal Control

01:24:49.189 --> 01:24:51.225
on macOS Monterey.

01:24:52.326 --> 01:24:54.461
Universal Control
makes it effortless

01:24:54.494 --> 01:24:55.929
to move between your devices

01:24:55.963 --> 01:24:58.699
so you can be more productive
and focus your energy

01:24:58.732 --> 01:25:00.601
on the task at hand.

01:25:00.634 --> 01:25:02.836
Another way our devices
work great together

01:25:02.870 --> 01:25:04.605
is with AirPlay.

01:25:04.638 --> 01:25:07.307
We all love the way AirPlay
lets us watch a movie

01:25:07.341 --> 01:25:08.509
or share a presentation

01:25:08.542 --> 01:25:11.245
from your iPhone to a TV
just like that.

01:25:11.278 --> 01:25:14.348
But there's another screen
with its stunning Retina display

01:25:14.381 --> 01:25:17.217
that makes everything you watch
simply amazing.

01:25:17.251 --> 01:25:18.752
That's why we're introducing

01:25:18.785 --> 01:25:20.954
AirPlay to Mac.

01:25:20.988 --> 01:25:23.090
It works just like AirPlay
today,

01:25:23.123 --> 01:25:25.058
so it's instantly familiar.

01:25:25.092 --> 01:25:28.529
You can play, present,
and share just about anything.

01:25:28.562 --> 01:25:30.430
As you draw a sketch on iPad,

01:25:30.464 --> 01:25:33.534
your colleagues can follow along
on the bigger display.

01:25:33.567 --> 01:25:37.037
And you can even take advantage
of any Mac's high-fidelity sound

01:25:37.070 --> 01:25:40.007
by using it as an AirPlay
speaker.

01:25:40.040 --> 01:25:43.877
AirPlay brings your Mac to life
in whole new ways.

01:25:43.911 --> 01:25:45.412
With macOS Monterey,

01:25:45.445 --> 01:25:47.915
your devices work together
like never before,

01:25:47.948 --> 01:25:50.551
making it more fluid
to work across them.

01:25:50.584 --> 01:25:53.854
And we're not just reinventing
how you work between devices.

01:25:53.887 --> 01:25:56.223
We're also giving you powerful
new tools

01:25:56.256 --> 01:25:59.259
to get more work done
on your devices.

01:25:59.293 --> 01:26:02.429
The Mac has a long, deep history
of automation

01:26:02.462 --> 01:26:04.264
with Command line,
shell scripts,

01:26:04.298 --> 01:26:06.266
AppleScript, and Automator.

01:26:06.300 --> 01:26:09.636
And on iOS, we've made
automation even easier

01:26:09.670 --> 01:26:10.637
with Shortcuts.

01:26:10.671 --> 01:26:14.107
Shortcuts takes all the taps
and swipes you usually need

01:26:14.141 --> 01:26:15.542
to order your favorite lunch

01:26:15.576 --> 01:26:17.711
and makes it as simple
as tapping a button

01:26:17.744 --> 01:26:19.446
or asking Siri.

01:26:19.479 --> 01:26:22.916
Shortcuts is all about
helping you get more done--

01:26:22.950 --> 01:26:23.817
faster.

01:26:23.851 --> 01:26:26.787
Because you can let your device
do the work for you.

01:26:26.820 --> 01:26:30.691
And this year, we're bringing
Shortcuts to the Mac.

01:26:30.724 --> 01:26:32.326
The Mac is, after all,

01:26:32.359 --> 01:26:34.361
where we turn for so much
of our creative work.

01:26:34.394 --> 01:26:36.864
And now you can automate
the everyday stuff

01:26:36.897 --> 01:26:39.299
to achieve peak productivity.

01:26:39.333 --> 01:26:42.469
You get access to a rich gallery
of pre-built shortcuts

01:26:42.503 --> 01:26:44.638
designed just for Mac.

01:26:44.671 --> 01:26:47.374
You can set up a shortcut to
instantly share selected files

01:26:47.407 --> 01:26:49.943
with your friends
so they never miss a moment.

01:26:49.977 --> 01:26:51.612
And with the Shortcuts Editor,

01:26:51.645 --> 01:26:53.981
you can easily link together
a series of actions

01:26:54.014 --> 01:26:57.284
to design shortcuts
for your specific workflows.

01:26:57.317 --> 01:26:58.952
For instance,
if you're a designer,

01:26:58.986 --> 01:27:00.654
get right to work
with a shortcut

01:27:00.687 --> 01:27:02.589
that opens Pinterest
in one window,

01:27:02.623 --> 01:27:04.191
Affinity Photo in another,

01:27:04.224 --> 01:27:06.894
and starts your favorite
playlist in Apple Music.

01:27:06.927 --> 01:27:08.462
All in one click.

01:27:08.495 --> 01:27:10.998
We've weaved Shortcuts
throughout macOS,

01:27:11.031 --> 01:27:13.467
so you can run them
no matter what app is open.

01:27:13.500 --> 01:27:15.636
They're in Finder, the Menu Bar,

01:27:15.669 --> 01:27:17.504
Spotlight, and of course,

01:27:17.538 --> 01:27:20.307
you can ask Siri to run them
hands-free.

01:27:20.340 --> 01:27:23.443
Shortcuts is the future
of automation on Mac,

01:27:23.477 --> 01:27:26.914
and this is just the start
of a multi-year transition.

01:27:26.947 --> 01:27:29.449
Automator will continue
to be supported,

01:27:29.483 --> 01:27:32.452
and you can import Automator
workflows into Shortcuts

01:27:32.486 --> 01:27:34.855
beginning day one.

01:27:34.888 --> 01:27:37.157
With Shortcuts,
there are more ways than ever

01:27:37.191 --> 01:27:39.293
to create, express yourself,

01:27:39.326 --> 01:27:41.328
and get stuff done.

01:27:41.361 --> 01:27:43.931
Finally, we have some
really big news

01:27:43.964 --> 01:27:46.800
about an app that's central
to the Mac experience--

01:27:46.834 --> 01:27:48.101
Safari.

01:27:48.135 --> 01:27:50.237
We built Safari
from the very beginning

01:27:50.270 --> 01:27:53.240
to provide the best
browsing experience on Mac,

01:27:53.273 --> 01:27:57.644
and it continues to blow the
competition out of the water.

01:27:57.678 --> 01:28:00.347
Safari is the world's fastest
browser.

01:28:00.380 --> 01:28:03.283
It makes navigating
even the most complex websites

01:28:03.317 --> 01:28:04.985
lightning fast.

01:28:05.018 --> 01:28:08.555
And Safari is known for its
legendary power efficiency.

01:28:08.589 --> 01:28:10.524
On an M1 MacBook Pro,

01:28:10.557 --> 01:28:14.494
Safari users can get
up to 17 hours of browsing

01:28:14.528 --> 01:28:17.164
And of course,
Safari sets the bar

01:28:17.197 --> 01:28:19.032
for user privacy on the web

01:28:19.066 --> 01:28:20.934
with features like
Privacy Report

01:28:20.968 --> 01:28:23.470
and Intelligent Tracking
Prevention.

01:28:23.504 --> 01:28:27.407
Our users are doing more in
the browser than ever before--

01:28:27.441 --> 01:28:31.245
work, school, shopping,
and entertainment.

01:28:31.278 --> 01:28:34.481
And that often leaves them
with a lot of tabs, windows,

01:28:34.515 --> 01:28:36.116
and other distractions.

01:28:36.149 --> 01:28:38.952
We think using the browser
should feel natural

01:28:38.986 --> 01:28:40.521
and uncluttered,

01:28:40.554 --> 01:28:43.123
so we've reimagined
the browsing experience.

01:28:43.156 --> 01:28:46.026
We distilled the toolbar
to is essential elements.

01:28:46.059 --> 01:28:48.962
Tabs are more compact,
modern, and lightweight.

01:28:48.996 --> 01:28:51.498
And there's a completely
new way to use tabs

01:28:51.532 --> 01:28:52.933
with Tab Groups.

01:28:52.966 --> 01:28:56.036
They allow you to easily save
and manage your tabs

01:28:56.069 --> 01:28:59.606
without cluttering up
your tab bar.

01:28:59.640 --> 01:29:03.443
I'll hand it over to Beth
to show it in action.

01:29:03.477 --> 01:29:04.378
[Beth] Thanks, Craig.

01:29:04.411 --> 01:29:05.913
Let's start with Safari's

01:29:05.946 --> 01:29:07.347
gorgeous new tab design.

01:29:07.381 --> 01:29:11.318
All of my tabs are right here
in the new streamlined tab bar.

01:29:11.351 --> 01:29:13.453
One of the really cool things
we did this year

01:29:13.487 --> 01:29:16.990
is we built the search field
right into the active tab.

01:29:17.024 --> 01:29:19.092
Safari is more space efficient
than ever,

01:29:19.126 --> 01:29:21.061
and I can see more of the page.

01:29:21.094 --> 01:29:24.131
I can click on the active tab
to see the page's full address,

01:29:24.164 --> 01:29:26.967
and then I can search
right from here.

01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:29.136
Reader is in the tab bar
whenever I need it,

01:29:29.169 --> 01:29:31.905
and everything else is
right here in the More menu.

01:29:31.939 --> 01:29:34.041
Check this out.
As I switch tabs,

01:29:34.074 --> 01:29:36.810
the tab bar takes on the color
of the site that I'm viewing,

01:29:36.844 --> 01:29:39.146
so it feels like
a part of the page.

01:29:39.179 --> 01:29:41.081
It looks beautiful.

01:29:41.648 --> 01:29:44.418
Next, I'm so excited
to tell you about Tab Groups.

01:29:44.451 --> 01:29:46.787
Tab Groups are an easy
and lightweight way

01:29:46.820 --> 01:29:49.122
to save your tabs
and pick them back up later.

01:29:49.156 --> 01:29:51.258
I'll open the new
redesigned side bar,

01:29:51.291 --> 01:29:53.594
and I have a few Tab Groups
here already.

01:29:53.627 --> 01:29:56.563
Each of these groups
is a whole set of tabs.

01:29:57.865 --> 01:29:59.666
I use them for meal planning,

01:29:59.700 --> 01:30:00.934
for news,

01:29:59.700 --> 01:30:00.934
for news,

01:30:00.968 --> 01:30:03.136
and gift shopping.

01:30:03.170 --> 01:30:04.605
Here in my open tabs,

01:30:04.638 --> 01:30:06.273
I'm planning a road trip
to Los Angeles,

01:30:06.306 --> 01:30:07.841
and I'm not done
with my research yet.

01:30:07.875 --> 01:30:09.309
I can save these into
a Tab Group

01:30:09.343 --> 01:30:10.711
and come back to it later.

01:30:10.744 --> 01:30:13.347
I'll click the new
Tab Group button

01:30:13.380 --> 01:30:16.183
and call this Trip to L.A.

01:30:17.017 --> 01:30:18.919
What's so powerful
about Tab Groups

01:30:18.952 --> 01:30:20.621
is that they're on
all of my devices.

01:30:20.654 --> 01:30:23.290
I've got my MacBook here,
and look.

01:30:23.323 --> 01:30:24.958
My new Tab Group
is here already.

01:30:24.992 --> 01:30:26.927
As I make changes
to my Tab Groups,

01:30:26.960 --> 01:30:28.729
they update everywhere.

01:30:28.762 --> 01:30:30.597
I'm gonna open a bunch of tabs,

01:30:30.631 --> 01:30:33.100
and my iMac
just keeps up.

01:30:33.133 --> 01:30:34.935
And if I change my current tab,

01:30:34.968 --> 01:30:36.770
my Tab Group is always
up to date,

01:30:36.803 --> 01:30:38.272
and I never miss a thing.

01:30:38.305 --> 01:30:40.774
I can't wait to share
these trip ideas with my family,

01:30:40.807 --> 01:30:43.277
and I can just drag this
Tab Group into an email

01:30:43.310 --> 01:30:45.179
and send it off.

01:30:46.847 --> 01:30:48.282
Once you start using Tab Groups,

01:30:48.315 --> 01:30:50.284
we know you're going to wanna
get to them all the time.

01:30:50.317 --> 01:30:52.386
So we made it super easy
to switch from right here

01:30:52.419 --> 01:30:54.221
in the tab bar.

01:30:54.254 --> 01:30:56.323
That's the new Safari on Mac.

01:30:56.356 --> 01:30:57.558
We didn't stop there, though.

01:30:57.591 --> 01:30:59.092
Back to Craig to tell you more.

01:30:59.126 --> 01:31:00.460
[Craig] Thanks, Beth.

01:31:00.494 --> 01:31:02.829
When we were designing
the new tab experience,

01:31:02.863 --> 01:31:05.365
we wanted to build something
that worked consistently

01:31:05.399 --> 01:31:08.635
when you switch from your Mac
to your iPhone or iPad.

01:31:08.669 --> 01:31:10.737
On iPad, the new tabs
and tab bar

01:31:10.771 --> 01:31:12.840
work just like they do on Mac.

01:31:12.873 --> 01:31:15.175
Tab Groups are especially
helpful on iPad,

01:31:15.209 --> 01:31:16.510
and the instant syncing

01:31:16.543 --> 01:31:19.580
means that you can continue
a project from anywhere.

01:31:19.613 --> 01:31:23.050
On iPhone, we've done
something really special.

01:31:23.083 --> 01:31:26.787
We took all the thinking
that went into Mac and iPad

01:31:26.820 --> 01:31:29.690
and pushed the envelope
even further.

01:31:29.723 --> 01:31:31.358
For this smaller screen size,

01:31:31.391 --> 01:31:33.694
we're introducing something
that's easier to reach

01:31:33.727 --> 01:31:36.296
and maximizes the page onscreen.

01:31:36.330 --> 01:31:38.832
The new tab bar appears
with just a tap

01:31:38.866 --> 01:31:40.834
and fits directly
under your thumb.

01:31:40.868 --> 01:31:44.538
And when you scroll, the bar
moves seamlessly out of the way.

01:31:44.571 --> 01:31:48.308
It's now easier and more natural
to access your other tabs too.

01:31:48.342 --> 01:31:50.310
You can just swipe over
on the tab bar

01:31:50.344 --> 01:31:52.012
to quickly move between them.

01:31:52.045 --> 01:31:53.447
Or swipe up on the tab bar

01:31:53.480 --> 01:31:56.383
to reveal a brand-new grid view
of all your tabs

01:31:56.416 --> 01:31:57.985
plus your Tab Groups.

01:31:58.018 --> 01:31:59.620
When you get to the end
of your tabs,

01:31:59.653 --> 01:32:01.889
you can swipe again
to open a new one,

01:32:01.922 --> 01:32:05.359
and the new customizable
start page syncs with Mac

01:32:05.392 --> 01:32:09.329
so you have the same Safari
experience everywhere.

01:32:09.363 --> 01:32:11.031
There's one last feature

01:32:11.064 --> 01:32:13.100
that we're really excited
to share--

01:32:13.133 --> 01:32:14.868
Extensions.

01:32:14.902 --> 01:32:18.038
Mac users love to deeply
customize Safari

01:32:18.071 --> 01:32:19.640
with extensions like Grammarly,

01:32:19.673 --> 01:32:21.175
Honey, and Momentum.

01:32:21.208 --> 01:32:25.279
And now, we're bringing web
extensions to iPhone and iPad.

01:32:25.312 --> 01:32:28.015
Just like on Mac,
you choose what websites

01:32:28.048 --> 01:32:29.750
you want extensions
to be active on,

01:32:29.783 --> 01:32:31.785
and developers
can easily tap into

01:32:31.818 --> 01:32:33.754
and entirely new audience

01:32:33.787 --> 01:32:35.656
because these extensions
can share code

01:32:35.689 --> 01:32:37.958
with existing Safari
web extensions.

01:32:37.991 --> 01:32:41.195
This is a huge year for Safari.

01:32:41.228 --> 01:32:44.264
A totally new tab design
and Tab Groups

01:32:44.298 --> 01:32:45.532
simplify your browsing.

01:32:45.566 --> 01:32:48.202
And Safari is more customizable
than ever

01:32:48.235 --> 01:32:49.436
with the new start page

01:32:49.469 --> 01:32:52.539
and extensions on iOS
and iPadOS.

01:32:52.573 --> 01:32:53.874
And with that,

01:32:53.907 --> 01:32:56.476
we have macOS Monterey.

01:32:56.510 --> 01:32:59.413
It's a fantastic release
with great new features

01:32:59.446 --> 01:33:02.015
that help Mac users do
more than ever.

01:33:02.049 --> 01:33:04.918
You can work across
Mac and your other devices

01:33:04.952 --> 01:33:07.888
using Universal Control
and AirPlay to Mac.

01:33:07.921 --> 01:33:11.191
It's easy to get productive
and creative using Shortcuts

01:33:11.225 --> 01:33:14.061
and a totally new design
for Safari,

01:33:14.094 --> 01:33:16.864
along with incredible features
like SharePlay,

01:33:16.897 --> 01:33:19.967
Shared with You, Focus,
and Quick Note.

01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:22.002
We do have more to share
with you,

01:33:22.035 --> 01:33:25.138
but first, let's get outta here.

01:33:25.172 --> 01:33:28.175
[upbeat music]

01:33:32.946 --> 01:33:35.215
Probably should've just taken
the car.

01:33:35.249 --> 01:33:37.017
As I mentioned a moment ago,

01:33:37.050 --> 01:33:39.520
we've made incredible advances
in macOS

01:33:39.553 --> 01:33:42.356
and across all of our platforms
this year.

01:33:42.389 --> 01:33:44.925
These are going to be amazing
for users,

01:33:44.958 --> 01:33:46.827
but they also create
new opportunities

01:33:46.860 --> 01:33:48.095
for our developers,

01:33:48.128 --> 01:33:50.597
the heart and soul of WWDC.

01:33:50.631 --> 01:33:52.966
And to tell you about
the new developer features,

01:33:53.000 --> 01:33:54.768
and technologies
we've been building

01:33:54.801 --> 01:33:57.504
to help you take your apps
to the next level,

01:33:57.538 --> 01:34:00.307
here's our VP of WWDR,

01:34:00.340 --> 01:34:03.644
Susan Prescott.

