01:41:34.962 --> 01:41:37.798
It integrates the Cloud
with our developer tools

01:41:37.831 --> 01:41:41.301
in a powerful new way,
and it's called...

01:41:41.335 --> 01:41:43.136
Xcode Cloud.

01:41:43.170 --> 01:41:45.939
Today, creating an app requires
multiple steps--

01:41:45.973 --> 01:41:48.242
building, testing,
and delivery--

01:41:48.275 --> 01:41:49.910
and a number of different tools.

01:41:49.943 --> 01:41:53.046
Xcode Cloud
simplifies the workflow

01:41:53.080 --> 01:41:55.082
by bringing everything together,

01:41:55.115 --> 01:41:56.984
so as an individual developer,

01:41:57.017 --> 01:41:59.253
you can focus your energy
on being creative

01:41:59.286 --> 01:42:02.523
and development teams can
collaborate more effectively.

01:42:02.556 --> 01:42:04.391
Here's how it works.

01:42:04.424 --> 01:42:06.727
When you commit a change
to your code,

01:42:06.760 --> 01:42:09.363
Xcode Cloud can automatically
build the app.

01:42:09.396 --> 01:42:11.231
Because it's built in the Cloud,

01:42:11.265 --> 01:42:13.333
your Mac is free
for other tasks.

01:42:13.367 --> 01:42:15.402
And for teams,
everyone can see

01:42:15.435 --> 01:42:16.837
if the change introduces errors,

01:42:16.870 --> 01:42:20.073
so everyone can find
and fix issues faster.

01:42:20.107 --> 01:42:24.178
Then Xcode Cloud runs
your automated tests in parallel

01:42:24.211 --> 01:42:26.413
so they complete
in a fraction of the time

01:42:26.446 --> 01:42:28.081
even as they simulate running

01:42:28.115 --> 01:42:31.018
on every kind of Apple device
and platform.

01:42:31.051 --> 01:42:34.188
And the test results
are displayed in Xcode,

01:42:34.221 --> 01:42:36.223
so you can easily see
what worked

01:42:36.256 --> 01:42:38.125
and fix what didn't.

01:42:38.158 --> 01:42:40.961
Finally, once the app
passes all its tests,

01:42:40.994 --> 01:42:43.497
Xcode Cloud can automatically
distribute it

01:42:43.530 --> 01:42:45.032
to the testers on your team,

01:42:45.065 --> 01:42:48.335
and even external beta testers,
with TestFlight.

01:42:48.368 --> 01:42:51.405
And all of these essential
continuous integration

01:42:51.438 --> 01:42:54.975
and delivery features
are right there in Xcode.

01:42:55.008 --> 01:42:57.511
So you can work
without switching tools

01:42:57.544 --> 01:42:59.279
and you can stay focused
on your code.

01:42:59.313 --> 01:43:02.716
Xcode Cloud is the quickest,
easiest way

01:43:02.749 --> 01:43:05.485
to build, test, and deliver
your apps.

01:43:05.519 --> 01:43:07.454
And it's built with
advanced security

01:43:07.487 --> 01:43:09.957
to protect you
and your projects.

01:43:09.990 --> 01:43:12.926
Your source code is only used in
a temporary build environment,

01:43:12.960 --> 01:43:15.429
and the only things
Xcode Cloud stores

01:43:15.462 --> 01:43:17.431
are the products of the build.

01:43:17.464 --> 01:43:19.299
Xcode Cloud and TestFlight

01:43:19.333 --> 01:43:21.768
make it easy to distribute betas
to users

01:43:21.802 --> 01:43:25.072
on iPhone, iPad,
Apple Watch, and Apple TV,

01:43:25.105 --> 01:43:27.741
and we want Xcode Cloud
to be able

01:43:27.774 --> 01:43:29.610
to automatically distribute
beta apps

01:43:29.643 --> 01:43:31.545
across all Apple platforms.

01:43:31.578 --> 01:43:33.380
To make that happen,

01:43:33.413 --> 01:43:36.149
we're bringing TestFlight
to the Mac.

01:43:36.183 --> 01:43:39.086
So you can use TestFlight
to easily test your Mac apps,

01:43:39.119 --> 01:43:41.421
including features like
In-app purchases.

01:43:41.455 --> 01:43:44.024
Xcode Cloud
is incredibly powerful,

01:43:44.057 --> 01:43:46.226
